<hr />

<h3>A. Sailing</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Move 1 to 7 spaces</li>
    <li>ships don't block other ships</li>
    <li>[red hand] locations cannot be skipped</li>
</ul>

<h3>B. Main Action</h3>
<div class="table">
    <div class="table-row">
        <div class="table-cell tc-6">
            <h4>2. City Actions</h4>
            <ol>
                <li>Deliver goods
                    <ul>
                        <li>Requires an empty space</li>
                        <li>Discard matching symbol to add disc</li>
                        <li>1 good max</li>
                        <li>Optional, may do action regardless</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li>Action
                    <ul>
                        <li>Not dependent on delivery</li>
                        <li>Action always follows delivery step</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ol>

            <h4>2. Village Action(s)</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Village location required (location without a scroll)</li>
                <li>for each village action, pick 1:
                    <ul>
                        <li>discard all cards for $2; min 1 card for money</li>
                        <li>take $1</li>
                        <li>buy a card: hand, planning area, prestige building</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ul>

            <h4>3. Quest</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Quest tile location required</li>
                <li>Pay cost, receive reward</li>
                <li>Take tile and add to ship board</li>
                <li>Score vp for X quests</li>
            </ul>

            <h4>4. Assistant Actions</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Assistant location required</li>
                <li>May only use assistants of your color</li>
                <li>Limit 1 assistant action per turn</li>
                <li>Assistants can share a space with other assistants, any color(s)</li>
                <li>2 vp for skipping your assistant</li>
            </ul>

            <h4>5. Homeward Bound</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Cannot skip, must end movement on each</li>
                <li>See Interim Scoring section</li>
            </ul>

        </div>
        <div class="table-cell tc-6">
            <h4>Combat</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Choose a nation, pay costs or take bonuses</li>
                <li>Most/least modifiers are ignored with ties</li>
                <li>Do any number of combat actions, no repeating</li>
                <li>A nation cannot displace its own cube</li>
                <li>Cannot "buy" combat points or figures leftover combat value</li>
                <li>All combat tokens gone <span class="arrow"></span> each nation has combat value 3</li>
            </ul>

            <h4>Exploring</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Cannot move backwards</li>
                <li>Skip occupied spaces, max 1 explorer per space</li>
                <li>Must move 1 space, may move less than maximum</li>
                <li>No rewards for moving through a space, only final space</li>
                <li>Do not replenish completed quests</li>
                <li>Red barrier: +3 influence with <i>one</i> nation</li>
                <li>Blue/Green barriers: 4vp for first to cross; 2vp otherwise</li>
                <li>Multiple players can share final space; 1 village action and score X vp</li>
            </ul>

            <h4>Free Actions</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Before, during, or after Main action</li>
                <li>Add a card to planning area</li>
                <li>Complete a career goal</li>
            </ul>

        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<h3>C. Draw Cards</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Draw to hand limit (4 or 6)</li>
    <li>May draw from deck (free) or take from display ($1 until ship is upgraded)</li>
    <li>Shuffle and create new draw pile if it runs out</li>
    <li>all players share the common draw pile and use a common discard pile</li>
</ul>

<hr />

<h3>Scoring</h3>
<div class="table">
    <div class="table-row">
        <div class="table-cell tc-6">
            <h4>Interim Scoring</h4>
            <p>Triggered when a ship ends movement on space 21a</p>
            <p>Start with player who triggered break</p>

            <ol>
                <li>Buy a card or prestige building, or 2 vp</li>
                <li>Receive money and points from income tracks</li>
                <li>Clear all delivered goods from cities</li>
                <li>Clear the display and draw 4 new cards</li>
                <li>Reveal the next prestige card</li>
                <li>Add new quests (non-campaign)</li>
                <li>Return <i>all</i> ships to Havana</li>
            </ol>

            <p>The next player begins the next round</p>

        </div>
        <div class="table-cell tc-6">
            <h4>Final Scoring</h4>
            <p>Triggered when a ship ends movement on space 22</p>

            <ol>
                <li>Same as interim</li>
                <li>Same as interim</li>
                <li>Score vp for cards in display</li>
                <li>For each nation, 3 vp for most influence (ties: all players get 3 vp)</li>
                <li>For each nation, score noble ranks:
                    <ul>
                        <li>N <span class="cross"></span> [E + M]</li>
                        <li>N: Noble Rank</li>
                        <li>E: # of empty cube spaces</li>
                        <li>M: Majority Bonus (# of ownership markers on board)
                            <ul>
                                <li>2-1-0</li>
                                <li>2-2-0</li>
                                <li>2-2-2</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<hr />

<h3>Expansion Modules</h3>

<h4>Home Port</h4>
<ul>
    <li>Deal 3 to each player when dealing career cards</li>
    <li>Choose 1 home port and add 2 discs</li>
    <li>New ship upgrade</li>
    <li>Immediate bonus and an ongoing bonus</li>
</ul>

<br />

<h4>Resistance Tile</h4>
<ul>
    <li>Flip resistance tile to show village action</li>
    <li>Liberate a location using any action with [cube slashed out icon]
        <ul>
            <li>project cards with the icon</li>
            <li>village action on the resistance tile</li>
            <li>legacy tile L40 from Uprising module</li>
            <li>combat action from Freeing the Carribbean module</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Remove cube, add to empty square in resistance tile, receive reward</li>
    <li>Adjacent cubes must be different colors
        <ul>
            <li>if unable to place: remove from game, receive no reward</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Fill 4 spaces <span class="arrow"></span> remove cubes from game, take $3 and 1 vp per combat token</li>
    <li><i>May</i> place ownership markers on resistance tile even if village action is still locked</li>
</ul>

<p>note: "displace" action from base game removes cube from the game; the cube does not go to resistance tile</p>
<p>note on Gravedigger (base game): the effect also triggers when liberating a location (not only when displacing)</p>

<br /><br />


<h4>Uprising</h4>
<ul>
    <li>Use legacy tile L40, always play together with Resistance Tile module</li>
    <li>Combat action: either fight <i>FOR</i> or <i>AGAINST</i> a nation</li>
    <li>Fighting <i>FOR</i>: base game rules apply</li>
    <li>Fighting <i>AGAINST</i>
        <ul>
            <li>Combat value is the same</li>
            <li>Bonuses for most/least are ignored</li>
            <li>Gain influence from the combat token <span class="arrow"></span> score 2 vp instead</li>
            <li>Base game combat actions (influence/annex/displace) are <b>not</b> available</li>
            <li>Combat actions gained via cards or ship upgrades are <b>not</b> available</li>
            <li>Liberate City and Liberate Village (on L40) are only options, limit 1 each</li>
            <li><b>Liberate City</b>
                <ul>
                    <li>1vp per city with <i>any</i> ownership marker</li>
                    <li>Remove cube of matching color from any <i>city</i>, place on resistance tile</li>
                    <li>Action is only available if you can remove an ownership marker</li>
                </ul>    
            </li>
            <li><b>Liberate Village</b> 
                <ul>
                    <li>Remove cube of matching color from any <i>village</i>, place on resistance tile</li>
                    <li>3vp per neighboring location with an ownership marker (of any color)</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ul>

<p>all card effects involving the combat action (and the "Galleon" card effects) are only available if fighting *for* a nation</p>
<p>cards that give combat points "before combat" can still be used (sailor, amaro pargo, etc.)</p>

